## Features

### pyproject.toml

To add extras from pproj to your project, add the following to your `pyproject.toml`:

```toml
[project.optional-dependencies]
dev = [
    "pproj",
]
```

### Makefile

```makefile
.PHONY: docs tests venv

brew:
	@proj $@ --command gh

browser:
	@$@

build:  # run: clean and venv (requirements)
	@$@

clean:
	@$@

commit: tests
	@$@

completions:
	@$@

coverage:
	@proj $@

docs:
	@$@

latest:
	@$@

next:
	@$@

pproj:
	@python3 -m pip install -q $@
    
publish:  # runs: tests (build (clean, venv (requirements)), pytest, ruff and tox), commit, tag, push, twine and clean
	@$@

pyenv:
	@pyenv install 3.11
	@pyenv install 3.12-dev

pytest:
	@proj $@

requirements:
	@$@ --install

ruff:
	@proj $@

secrets:
	@$@

tests:  # runs: build (clean, venv (requirements)), pytest, ruff and tox
	@$@

tox:
	@proj $@

twine:
	@proj $@

venv:  # runs: requirements
	@$@

.DEFAULT_GOAL := publish
```

## Installation

You can install _Pproj_ via [pip] from [PyPI]:

```console
$ pip install pproj
```

